OL,3,CFirst conviction linked to Post Office
OL,4,CCapture referred to Court of Appeal
OL,6,FThe first criminal conviction linked
OL,7,Fto the Post Office Capture system has
OL,8,Fbeen referred to the Court of Appeal.
OL,10,FThe Criminal Cases Review Commission
OL,11,F(CCRC) said the case of Patricia Owen,
OL,12,Fwho was found guilty of five counts of
OL,13,Ftheft in June 1998, has been referred
OL,14,Fon the grounds that it was an abuse of
OL,15,Fprocess.
OL,17,FMrs Owen pleaded not guilty to all
OL,18,Ffive charges after the Broad Oak Post
OL,19,FOffice branch in Sweechgate,
OL,20,FCanterbury, was left with a shortfall
OL,21,Fof #6,000.
