OL,6,F"It is important to recognise that we
OL,7,Fawait the Post Office's position on
OL,8,Fthis matter, and whether it will offer
OL,9,Fany evidence against Mrs Owen's
OL,10,Fconviction being overturned, and then
OL,11,Fof course the Court of Appeal's
OL,12,Fdecision itself.
OL,14,F"I was always struck by how Mrs Owen
OL,15,Fprotested her innocence throughout,
OL,16,Fpointing the finger of blame at the
OL,17,Fsystem.
OL,19,F"Why compelling IT evidence was not
OL,20,Fused in court remains a mystery.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU{D@AOU
